# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║  Esaku — Environment Configuration                         ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# The app auto-detects the database engine:
#   - If DB_HOST is set → uses MySQL
#   - If DB_HOST is empty → uses SQLite (local dev)

# ── Server ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=development
JWT_SECRET=change-me-to-a-random-string

# ── Admin Account ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set these to create an admin user on first boot.
# If left empty, no admin is created automatically.
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@esaku.xyz
ADMIN_PASSWORD=root1234!

# ── Database: SQLite (Development) ──────────────────────────────
# No config needed — SQLite is the default.
# Data is stored in ./data/esaku.sqlite
# DB_FILE=./data/esaku.sqlite

# ── Database: MySQL (Production — Hostinger) ────────────────────
# Uncomment and fill these to switch to MySQL.
# Once DB_HOST is set, the app automatically uses MySQL.
#
# DB_CLIENT=mysql
# DB_HOST=srv123.hstgr.io
# DB_PORT=3306
# DB_USER=u123456789_esaku
# DB_PASSWORD=your_mysql_password_here
# DB_NAME=u123456789_esaku
